		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Parsimony</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="infobox sisterproject">
<div style="float: left;">
<div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Wiktionary-logo-en.svg" class="image" title="Wiktionary-logo-en.svg"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/Wiktionary-logo-en.svg/50px-Wiktionary-logo-en.svg.png" width="50" height="54" border="0" /></a></div>
</div>
<div style="margin-left: 60px;">Look up <i><b><a href="http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/parsimony" class="extiw" title="wiktionary:parsimony">parsimony</a></b></i> in <a href="/wiki/Wiktionary" title="Wiktionary">Wiktionary</a>, the free dictionary.</div>
</div>
<p><b>Parsimony</b> is a 'less is better' concept of <a href="/wiki/Frugality" title="Frugality">frugality</a>, economy or caution in arriving at a hypothesis or course of action. The word derives from Middle English <i>parcimony</i>, from Latin <i>parsimonia</i>, from <i>parsus</i>, past participle of <i>parcere</i>: <b>to spare</b>. It is a general principle that has applications from science to philosophy and all related fields. Parsimony is essentially the implementation of <a href="/wiki/Occam%27s_razor" title="Occam's razor">Occam's razor</a>.</p>
